description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have two vacancies for (LAS) Locum Appointment for Service doctors at Foundation Year One Level. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;These are fixed-term posts for a period of 4 months to commence 2 December 2020 until 6 April 2021. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;The vacant posts comprise the following Specialties:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Respiratory; Surgery&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a friendly, supportive environment and have an active Postgraduate Medical Centre, with a small team of friendly staff who are regularly praised for their high level of support and pastoral care to the foundation doctors&lt;strong&gt;. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But don&#39;t just take our word for it -&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&quot;Being a LAS FY1 I was given similar opportunities and support as were given to my trainee colleagues. This helped me to get my FY2 training post and I chose to work in this hospital located in the beautiful historic city of Hereford again.&quot; Dr Rajani Gurung&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&quot;I first started working in Hereford County Hospital as an FY1 in July 2017. That was my first job as a doctor and I was a little worried about how the working environment was going to be like. Despite the worry inside me, I hoped for the best and started my career. I felt welcomed straight away, all the staff were friendly and helpful.&quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;APPLICANTS MUST HAVE FULL GMC REGISTRATION WITH A LICENCE TO PRACTISE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For informal enquiries please contact the Foundation Year 1 Programme Director&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Dr Jo Connell, email &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;joanne.connell@wvt.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
